A massive tangled web of obsolete computer cables, punch cards, and floppy disks spilling out of a crumbling neoclassical government building with grand columns, rendered in vintage 1970s illustration style with muted ochre, olive green, and burnt orange tones. Paper forms flutter through the air like confused birds while an ancient mainframe computer sits abandoned on the marble steps, its reels still spinning uselessly. The scene has the aesthetic of a faded government pamphlet or old magazine editorial illustration, with visible halftone dot patterns and slightly yellowed paper texture throughout.
